---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { defaultLang } from '../i18n/ui';
---
<Layout title="About the Archive | Sinpes" description="The mission behind the Sinpes open-source typography archive." locale={defaultLang}>
  <main class="view-container legal-page">
    <h1>About Sinpes</h1>
    <p>Founded as a response to the fragmentation of digital type foundries, Sinpes was established to curate the world's finest open-source letterforms. Our mission goes beyond aggregation; we perform rigorous typographic auditing to ensure absolute pixel-perfection for both high-resolution digital interfaces and print editorial workflows.</p>
    
    <h2>Our Curatorial Standards</h2>
    <p>We recognize that typography is the foundational architecture of visual communication. Unlike automated aggregators that indiscriminately scrape font data, every typeface archived on Sinpes is subjected to a comprehensive technical review. We meticulously verify kerning tables, glyph completeness, hinting instructions, and OpenType features. Only fonts that meet our stringent criteria for production-readiness are admitted into the archive.</p>
    
    <h2>The Open Source Imperative</h2>
    <p>At Sinpes, we believe that premium design tools should not be gated by prohibitive licensing fees. By archiving typefaces exclusively licensed under the SIL Open Font License (OFL), Apache 2.0, and similar permissive agreements, we aim to democratize access to exceptional typography. We ensure that independent creators, software engineers, and enterprise design studios alike have unrestricted access to world-class letterforms for commercial and personal applications.</p>
    
    <h2>Technical Infrastructure</h2>
    <p>Our distribution pipeline is engineered for maximum performance and reliability. We provide highly optimized, web-ready WOFF2 formats tailored for modern front-end architectures, alongside pristine OTF and TTF masters for print designers. Every download is bundled with transparent licensing documentation, safeguarding your commercial projects against intellectual property infringement.</p>
  </main>
</Layout>

<style>
  .legal-page { padding: 80px 24px; max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto; border-left: 0.5px solid var(--rule); border-right: 0.5px solid var(--rule); min-height: 60vh; }
  h1 { font-size: 48px; margin-bottom: 32px; letter-spacing: -0.02em; font-weight: 500; }
  h2 { font-size: 12px; margin-top: 48px; margin-bottom: 16px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.1em; color: var(--muted); font-weight: 600; }
  p { font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 24px; color: var(--fg); max-width: 700px; }
  .last-updated { font-size: 14px; color: var(--muted); margin-bottom: 48px; }
</style>
